adjective.description: Higher in rank, status, or quality.
examples: it is superior to every other car on the road

adjective.description: Having or showing an overly high opinion of oneself; supercilious.
(of a letter, figure, or symbol) written or printed above the line.
Further above or out; higher in position.

noun.description: A person or thing superior to another in rank, status, or quality, especially a colleague in a higher position.
A superior letter, figure, or symbol.

proper noun.description: A port city in northwestern Wisconsin, on Lake Superior, adjacent to Duluth in Minnesota; population 26,223 (est. 2008).

origin: Late Middle English: from Old French superiour, from Latin superior, comparative of superus that is above, from super above.
